<StackPanel
    x:Class="UnitedSets.UI.Controls.HomeBackground"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    VerticalAlignment="Center"
    Grid.Row="1"
    HorizontalAlignment="Center"
    Canvas.ZIndex="-1"
>
    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal" HorizontalAlignment="Center">
        <Image x:Name="AppFontIcon"
                HorizontalAlignment="Left" 
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Source="ms-appx:///Assets/SmallTile.scale-400.png"   
                Width="48" 
                Height="48"/>
        <TextBlock
                Text="United Sets"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                
                FontSize="28"/>
        <!--Margin="8, 0, 0, 0"-->
        <TextBlock
                Text="{StaticResource AppVersion}"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Margin="8, 6, 0, 0"
                Opacity="0.7"
                FontSize="24"/>
    </StackPanel>
    <StackPanel Orientation="Vertical" HorizontalAlignment="Center">
        <TextBlock FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0, 0, 0, 4">Tips:</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock>
        • Drag a Tab out to release the Window
        <LineBreak/>• Double Click On the Tab for more customization
        </TextBlock>
        <TextBlock FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#e96e60" Margin="0, 12, 0, 4">Preview Warnings:</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Center">
        • May not work well with UWP windows
        <LineBreak/>• [Experimental] Save and Close may sometimes fail to add
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;windows back to United Sets.
        <LineBreak/>• [Experimental] Save and Close will NOT work for system
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;UWP or Packaged apps (like Calculator/Paint/Notepad/etc)
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;and one-process-only app (like File Explorer).
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;(It will still work for user installed ones)
        <LineBreak/>• [Experimental] Removing title bar makes them undragable
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;sometimes. Therefore, it is advised not to do that for
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;windows in the Splitable Tab. If you did, you can detach or
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;remove it from the tab customization menu.
        </TextBlock>
        <TextBlock FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0, 12, 0, 4">Hotkeys:</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock>
        • [SHIFT] + "New Tab + Icon": Create Splitable Tab
        <LineBreak/>• Hold [CTRL] while dragging window on top of United Sets:
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;add that window to United Sets
        <LineBreak/>• Hold [SHIFT] while opening United Sets:
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;separate app taskbar icons
        <LineBreak/>• Hold [ALT] while adding a window:
        <LineBreak/>&#160;&#160;add window in a borderless mode
        </TextBlock>
    </StackPanel>
</StackPanel>
